{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.35",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 35,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 35",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 35 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:1",
      "text": "And Elius resumed and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:2",
      "text": "What is this that thou thinkest to be according to right? who art thou that thou hast said, I am righteous before the Lord?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:4",
      "text": "I will answer thee, and thy three friends.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:5",
      "text": "Look up to the sky and see; and consider the clouds, how high they are above thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:6",
      "text": "If thou hast sinned, what wilt thou do? and if too thou hast transgressed much, what canst thou perform?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:7",
      "text": "And suppose thou art righteous, what wilt thou give him? or what shall he receive of thy hand?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:8",
      "text": "Thy ungodliness may affect a man who is like to thee; or thy righteousness a son of man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:9",
      "text": "They that are oppressed of a multitude will be ready to cry out; they will call for help because of the arm of many.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:10",
      "text": "But none said, Where is God that made me, who appoints the night-watches;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:11",
      "text": "who makes me to differ from the four-footed beasts of the earth, and from the birds of the sky?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:12",
      "text": "There they shall cry, and none shall hearken, even because of the insolence of wicked men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:13",
      "text": "For the Lord desires not to look on error, for he is the Almighty One.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:14",
      "text": "He beholds them that perform lawless deeds, and he will save me: and do thou plead before him, if thou canst praise him, as it is possible even now.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:15",
      "text": "For he is not now regarding his wrath, nor has he noticed severely any trespass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.35.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:16",
      "text": "Yet Job vainly opens his mouth, in ignorance he multiplies words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
